Blood Pressure Tracker

This is a blood pressure tracker application built with Streamlit, Pandas, and Matplotlib. It allows users to input their blood pressure readings, along with optional weight, pulse, and feeling information. The application displays the recorded data in tabular format and visualizes it using line and box plots.
Features

    Add blood pressure readings with optional weight, pulse, and feeling information
    Visualize blood pressure data over time using line and box plots
    Display the recorded data in tabular format

Installation

    Install Python 3.7 or higher

    Clone this repository:

    $git clone https://github.com/yourusername/blood-pressure-tracker.git

Change to the application directory:

    $cd blood-pressure-tracker

Create a virtual environment:

    Â§python -m venv venv

Activate the virtual environment:

    Windows:

    $venv\Scripts\activate

macOS/Linux:

    $source venv/bin/activate

Install the required packages:

    $pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the application:

    $streamlit run bloodpressure.py

Usage

    Open your web browser and visit the Streamlit app at http://localhost:8501
    Input your blood pressure readings (systolic and diastolic) along with optional weight, pulse, and feeling information in the sidebar
    Click "Submit" to save the data
    View the recorded data in the main application window, where it will be displayed in both tabular format and visualized using line and box plots

Dependencies

    Streamlit
    Pandas
    Matplotlib
    Seaborn

